\begin{abstract}
It is commonly assumed that Shor's quantum algorithm
for the efficient factorization of a large number $N$ requires a pure initial
state. Here we demonstrate that a single pure qubit together with a collection
of $log_2 N$ qubits in an arbitrary mixed state is sufficient to implement Shor's
factorization algorithm efficiently.
\end{abstract}


